= arena =
 == to get a prototype working ==
 * chat scroll down when other people talk only if the scroll bar is at the 
   bottom.
 * make the gui usable
   > competition page
 * deploy
 * make the gui pretty
   > award star with a number in it next to person's name instead of parens
   > thumbs ups instead of voting
 * dummy about, policy, settings pages

 == improvements ==
 * uploading an entry should clear that form
 * paging on competitions. right now it sends them all.
 * display error when chat message doesn't go through
 * the online users is sketchy at best
 * have a robust song player and use it during competitions
 * mute button on player
 * chat: handle join/part messages by removing them or adding them from
   the onliners list
 * cron job to delete users who register and don't activate after a certain
   period of time. or just allow their accounts to be overwritten if they
   are old.
 * user profile page
   - show their competition entries
 * edit competition
 * make the gui pretty
 * support some kind of formatting for author comments and such. minimum:
   honor line breaks. maximum: a bb-like system or markdown.
 * compo owner gets skip song controls
 * compo owner can make other people moderators too
 * listening party - make song comments during chat during listening party
 * use === instead of ==
 * better competition ordering in arena

 * protect against h4xz0rz by adding a @method to views which do things like
   login, logout, etc. The method would make sure the referrer was us and not
   some other website.
 * moderation tools for competitions
 * obfuscate media URLs to protect people's stuff
 * provide some way to format themes, rules, comments, etc
 * chat colors
 * chat: display how many invisible observers there are
 * color the time differently when there isn't much time left so that 
   people know they're running out of time
 * better feedback for a failed submission than an alert box.
 * make the gui experience of clicking edit on a submission and then
   deciding not to better.
 * replay listening party feature
  - put an indicator on the page so you know whether it's live or replay
 * settings page
 * put whitelist/blacklist/open in the create competition page. default open.
 * test with a messed up clock in windows
   - possibly use ajax to improve offset calculation between server and local.
 * google map integration
 * rss feed for competitions
 * show and allow posting comments on songs on user pages
 * song wave form

